With tags. 26.5” scale length Deep-cutaway mahogany body Nitro Wizard 3-piece maple/purpleheart neck Birdseye Maple fingerboard with 24 jumbo frets, black offset dot inlays, and luminescent side dot inlays DiMarzio Fusion Edge neck and bridge humbucking pickups Gibraltar Standard II-7 bridge Gotoh MG-T locking machine heads Factory Tuning: 1D, 2A, 3F, 4C, 5G, 6D, 7A Black hardware If you play down-tuned metal on a 7-string, Ibanez has designed a guitar just for you. With its 26.5" scale length, the RGD Iron Label RGDIR7M is optimized for the heaviest music styles, executing every note with precision and power. The fast Nitro Wizard neck, topped with a sleek birdseye maple fingerboard, plays beautifully, while the instrument's deep cutaways give you unrestricted access to the upper registers. The RGDIR7M's DiMarzio Fusion Edge pickups deliver powerful scooped tone with tight, compressed bass response and crisp high-end bite, while its Gibraltar Standard II-7 bridge and Gotoh MG-T locking machine heads provide rock-solid tuning stability and monumental sustain. The Ibanez RGD Iron Label RGDIR7M is a progressive metal player's dream come true.
